# Portable defaults work without editing: the connector falls back to
# .connector-state/ for tiny no-network fixture runs.
#
# For larger local runs, set these to external storage. On this host a suitable
# example is /srv/abyss-machine/storage/connectors/aoa-telegram-connector, but public
# clones should choose their own paths.

# CONNECTOR_FAMILY_ROOT=/path/to/connector-databases
# CONNECTOR_INSTANCE_ROOT=${CONNECTOR_FAMILY_ROOT}/aoa-telegram-connector
# CONNECTOR_DATA_ROOT=${CONNECTOR_INSTANCE_ROOT}/data
# CONNECTOR_CACHE_ROOT=${CONNECTOR_INSTANCE_ROOT}/cache
# CONNECTOR_ARTIFACT_ROOT=${CONNECTOR_INSTANCE_ROOT}/artifacts

# Optional MTProto connected-account pilot. Keep these in a local vault/env
# file, never in Git.
# TELEGRAM_API_ID=123456
# TELEGRAM_API_HASH=replace-with-my-telegram-api-hash
# TELEGRAM_PHONE=+10000000000

# Optional owned-source base. This is generated by `aoa-telegram sources add`
# under CONNECTOR_DATA_ROOT/sources/ and should stay local.
# AOA_TELEGRAM_SOURCE_REGISTRY=${CONNECTOR_DATA_ROOT}/sources/telegram_sources.json
